-- Shares of Turkey's Migros jump 10.2 pct after Anadolu bids to buy 40 pct stake
-- By Seda Sezer
-- Fri Oct 03, 2014 02:40AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Oct 3 (Reuters) - Turkish retailer Migros <MGROS.IS> shares jumped 10.2 percent on Friday after Turkish conglomerate Anadolu Group offered to buy a 40.25 percent stake in the supermarket chain from BC Partners [BCPRT.UL].

Migros shares rose to 21.05 lira at the open of trade in Istanbul. [ID:nL2N0RY088]